        },
        "subject": "LU-12632 tests: stop running sanity-hsm 90 for ZFS",
        "message": "LU-12632 tests: stop running sanity-hsm 90 for ZFS\n\nWith ZFS 0.8.1, sanity-hsm test 90 is failing an excessive\nnumber of times; over 30% of the time.  We need to stop\nrunning sanity-hsm test 90, put it on the ALWAYS_EXCEPT\nlist, until we understand how to fix this issue.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial fstype=ldiskfs testlist=sanity-hsm\nTest-Parameters: fstype=zfs testlist=sanity-hsm\nSigned-off-by: James Nunez <jnunez@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I777e1d3ebe019183a827f6e2f56278f4bd65e99d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
